org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the Matter of the Application of MIKE OUMPU, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus.

Comes now the respondent Henry M. White by his attorneys and demurs to the complaint or application of the above named Mike Oumpu for a writ of habeas corpus herein upon the following grounds, to-wit:
That said application or complaint does not state facts sufficient to constitute a cause of action herein.
That said application or complaint shows upon its face that the said applicant for a writ of habeas corpus is not entitled to the relief prayed for in said complaint.

That the said application or complain shows upon the face thereof that this court has no jurisdiction to hear or determine the matters herein in this, that the said application or complaint shows that the Secretary of Labor has never passed upon nor taken any final action with relation to the deportation of said applicant for said writ of ha beas corpus.
